So `xs.head! ≤ ys.head!`.
By transitivity, `ys.head! ≤ x`.
So `leftmin ys` holds.

If `xs` is empty, then `xs ++ ys = ys`.
`h` becomes `∀ x ∈ ys, (ys).head! ≤ x`.
This is exactly `leftmin ys`.
